2. Fix tasks/validate.yml for extra blocks

Your current validation requires every extra block to use item.block. That is fine, but earlier the script used content, which caused the failure.

You can either enforce block only, or support both block and content.

I’d support both so the role is more forgiving.

Replace the Validate each extra block entry task with this:

- name: Validate each extra block entry
  ansible.builtin.assert:
    that:
      - item.name is defined
      - item.name | string | length > 0
      - item.marker is defined
      - item.marker | string | length > 0
      - item.block is defined or item.content is defined
      - (item.block | default(item.content) | string) | length > 0
    fail_msg: >-
      Invalid group_vars_defaults_extra_blocks entry:
      {{ item | to_nice_yaml(indent=2) }}
      Each extra block must define name, marker, and either block or content.
  loop: "{{ group_vars_defaults_extra_blocks }}"
  loop_control:
    label: "{{ item.name | default('missing-name') }}"
  when: group_vars_defaults_manage_extra_blocks | bool

3. Fix tasks/extra_blocks.yml

Update this so it also supports either block or content.

Replace the file with:

# UNCLASSIFIED
- name: Manage generic extra blocks
  ansible.builtin.blockinfile:
    path: "{{ group_vars_defaults_file }}"
    marker: "{{ item.marker }}"
    insertafter: EOF
    backup: "{{ group_vars_defaults_backup | bool }}"
    block: "{{ item.block | default(item.content) }}"
  loop: "{{ group_vars_defaults_extra_blocks }}"
  loop_control:
    label: "{{ item.name }}"
# UNCLASSIFIED

4. Keep nfs_mount_defaults.yml mostly as-is

Your nfs_mount_defaults.yml looks okay. It removes the old top-level keys and then writes a managed block.

I would not rewrite that right now.

The important part is that it should now write into:

aerolit_bootstrap_generated.yml

not directly into:

workstation_defaults.yml

That prevents the messy repeated blocks you saw earlier.

5. Important warning about file order

Since you chose:

aerolit_bootstrap_generated.yml

instead of:

zz_aerolit_bootstrap_generated.yml

then this file will likely load before:

workstation_defaults.yml

So if both files define the same variable, workstation_defaults.yml may override the generated file.

That means you should remove old generated values from workstation_defaults.yml, especially these:

path_for_ansible:
mount_point_setup_single_site_mounts:
enable_epel:
aerolit_yum_repositories:

At minimum, remove the broken raw marker section:

AEROLIT YUM REPOSITORIES
aerolit_yum_repositories:
  ...
AEROLIT YUM REPOSITORIES

That is invalid YAML and must not stay in workstation_defaults.yml.

